EcosystemLevelJustification: The Boreal-Transition Alvar is a non-forested to sparsely treed (<60% tree cover) ecosystem type. Canadian ecosystem experts reached consensus that the International Vegetation Classification (IVC) Group level is ideal for KBAs based on non-forest ecosystem types. The Group level corresponds to Level 5 (global ecosystem types) in the IUCN Global Ecosystem Typology, which is appropriate for global ecosystem KBAs according to the KBA Standard and Guidelines.
